@jihoonson thanks for the comment. In `getCurrentTotalStats()` in `KafkaSupervisor` the code

```java
    for (int groupId : pendingCompletionTaskGroups.keySet()) {
       TaskGroup group = taskGroups.get(groupId);
```

loops over the group IDs of pendingCompletionTaskGroups, but tries to get a group from taskGroup instead of pendingCompletionTaskGroups. This causes a `NullPointerException` since these 2 groups are supposed be disjoint.

